prompts.text:
You can easily run this workflow here:

https://www.runcomfy.com/comfyui-workflows/comfyui-animatediff-workflow-stable-diffusion-animation

It's a ComfyUI cloud environment, all the necessary nodes and models for customers are set up and ready to use. So there's no need to install anything.




Video Length

Batch Size determines animation length! Longer lengths will create multiple AnimateDiff "scenes", which are "stitched" using the Uniform Context Options.

Uniform Context Options control the transition between the stitched "scenes"

There is no limit to the amount of latents you can pass in, so unlimited animation length is possible. The flow defaults to values which produce good, short, results.

Video Lengths -
Batch size 16 produces a 2 second video
Batch Size 32 Produces a 4 second video
Batch size 64 produces a 8 second video



Upscale
Upscaling can be turned on/off by Activating/Bypassing the nodes.


Motion LoRA
The AnimateDiff LoRA Loader can be enabled if you wish to use Motion LoRA.
